# Keep the MCP image build context small. The Dockerfile COPYs only core.py,
# mcp_server/, and the small prepared data files (impact_summary.csv, app_data/,
# mcp_data/). Everything below is dashboard code, dev/QA tooling, or raw data the
# server never reads at request time.

# --- version control / caches ---
.git
.gitignore
**/__pycache__
*.pyc
.pytest_cache
.playwright-mcp
.venv
venv
venv_*

# --- dashboard (not part of the MCP runtime) ---
app.py
pages/
utils.py
.streamlit/
qa_screenshots/
qa_dashboard.py

# --- dev / QA / eval tooling ---
tests/
eval/
requirements-dev.txt
.env
*.env

# --- raw + intermediate data the server never reads ---
data/monthly_orders/
data/outputs/orders_compiled_enriched.csv

# --- misc ---
.python-version
README.md
CLAUDE.md
analysis.py
prepare_app_data.py
